Zunou Pulse API

The zunou pulse api documentation

API Endpoints
http://localhost:8000/graphql

Queries

activeThread

Description

Find a single thread by ID.

Response

Returns a Thread

Arguments
Name Description
pulseId - String! Search by organization key.
organizationId - String! Search by organization key.
type - ThreadType! type user thread

Example

Query
query activeThread(
  $pulseId: String!,
  $organizationId: String!,
  $type: ThreadType!
) {
  activeThread(
    pulseId: $pulseId,
    organizationId: $organizationId,
    type: $type
  ) {
    createdAt
    id
    name
    organizationId
    type
    updatedAt
    pulseId
    userId
    isActive
    user {
      ...UserFragment
    }
    savedMessages {
      ...SavedMessageFragment
    }
    pulse {
      ...PulseFragment
    }
  }
}
Variables
{
  "pulseId": "abc123",
  "organizationId": "xyz789",
  "type": "user"
}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "activeThread": {
      "createdAt": "2007-12-03T10:15:30Z",
      "id": "67728829-c6e8-4958-9098-c74e693d53ad",
      "name": "xyz789",
      "organizationId": "67728829-c6e8-4958-9098-c74e693d53ad",
      "type": "abc123",
      "updatedAt": "2007-12-03T10:15:30Z",
      "pulseId": "67728829-c6e8-4958-9098-c74e693d53ad",
      "userId": "67728829-c6e8-4958-9098-c74e693d53ad",
      "isActive": true,
      "user": User,
      "savedMessages": [SavedMessage],
      "pulse": Pulse
    }
  }
}
Queries

activities

Description

List multiple feed available for a pulse.

Response

Returns [Activity!]!

Arguments
Name Description
organizationId - String! Filters by organization ID.
receiverId - String! Filters by receiver ID

Example

Query
query activities(
  $organizationId: String!,
  $receiverId: String!
) {
  activities(
    organizationId: $organizationId,
    receiverId: $receiverId
  ) {
    id
    description
    causer {
      ...UserFragment
    }
    subjectType
    organizationId
    pulseId
    receiverId
    properties
    feedType
    createdAt
    updatedAt
  }
}
Variables
{
  "organizationId": "xyz789",
  "receiverId": "abc123"
}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "activities": [
      {
        "id": "4",
        "description": "xyz789",
        "causer": User,
        "subjectType": "xyz789",
        "organizationId": 4,
        "pulseId": "4",
        "receiverId": 4,
        "properties": {},
        "feedType": "TASK_CREATED",
        "createdAt": "2007-12-03T10:15:30Z",
        "updatedAt": "2007-12-03T10:15:30Z"
      }
    ]
  }
}

Queries

agents

Description

List multiple agents.

Response

Returns an AgentPaginator!

Arguments
Name Description
name - String Filters by name. Accepts SQL LIKE wildcards % and _.
organizationId - String Filters by organization ID.
first - Int! Limits number of fetched items. Default = 10
page - Int The offset from which items are returned.

Example

Query
query agents(
  $name: String,
  $organizationId: String,
  $first: Int!,
  $page: Int
) {
  agents(
    name: $name,
    organizationId: $organizationId,
    first: $first,
    page: $page
  ) {
    paginatorInfo {
      ...PaginatorInfoFragment
    }
    data {
      ...AgentFragment
    }
  }
}
Variables
{
  "name": "xyz789",
  "organizationId": "abc123",
  "first": 10,
  "page": 987
}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "agents": {
      "paginatorInfo": PaginatorInfo,
      "data": [Agent]
    }
  }
}

Description

The ID scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as "4") or integer (such as 4) input value will be accepted as an ID.
